Here's a minimal API endpoint handling multipart form uploads with images + a description:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Features;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size to 50 MB
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFileCollection files, HttpRequest request) =>
{
    var description = request.Form["description"].ToString();

    if (files.Count == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("No files uploaded.");

    var allowed = new[] { "image/jpeg", "image/png", "image/gif", "image/webp" };
    var saved = new List<string>();

    foreach (var file in files)
    {
        if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType))
            return Results.BadRequest($"Invalid content type: {file.ContentType}");

        var path = Path.Combine("uploads", $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{Path.GetExtension(file.FileName)}");
        Directory.CreateDirectory("uploads");

        await using var stream = File.Create(path);
        await file.CopyToAsync(stream);
        saved.Add(path);
    }

    return Results.Ok(new { description, fileCount = saved.Count, paths = saved });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()                          // needed for bare API calls
.WithRequestFormLimits(multipartBodyLengthLimit: 50 * 1024 * 1024);

app.Run();
```

**Key pieces:**

| Concern | How it's handled |
|---|---|
| **50 MB limit** | `MaxRequestBodySize` on Kestrel + `WithRequestFormLimits` on the endpoint |
| **Multiple files** | Bind `IFormFileCollection` — ASP.NET reads all `<input type="file">` parts |
| **Text field** | Read `request.Form["description"]` from the same multipart form |
| **Content-type check** | Allowlist of image MIME types before saving |
| **Anti-forgery** | `.DisableAntiforgery()` since this is a pure API (no Razor pages) |

Test with `curl`:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/upload \
  -F "files=@photo1.jpg" \
  -F "files=@photo2.png" \
  -F "description=Vacation photos"
```
